This is a Django application for the CRAMS Provision

Getting Started
---------------

Set up a virtualenv and create py35 virtualenv

# Install python3.5

# Run flake8

tox -e flake8

# Run test

tox -e py35

* Copy local_settings.py.example to local_settings.py
* Modify it to point a desired keystone server and crams db api server.

# Start crams provision cron job

# Install django-crontab

# add django-crontab to installed apps in django settings.py:

INSTALLED_APPS = (
    'django_crontab',
    ...
)

#define your cron job module and  add this to your settings.py:

CRONJOBS = [
    ('*/5 * * * *', 'nc_provision.cron.provision.provision_cron_job', '&> /tmp/crams_provision.log')
]

# Please see settings for more details

# github reference at https://github.com/kraiz/django-crontab

# To add all defined jobs from CRONJOBS to crontab (of the user which you are running this command with):

python manage.py crontab add

# show current active jobs of this project:

python manage.py crontab show

# removing all defined jobs is straight forward:

python manage.py crontab remove



